    <note>Qian(1) Shouzhi [17946] Wang Yingchen, WJ, 23.285-6 (wife, born Lu(9), who married him at age 18 and died in 1148 at age 48). According to Wang Yingchen, who obviously considered this a marriage down for born Lu(9), the Qian and Lu were hereditarily intermarried (shiyin). In fact, Qian Xie [145] was L?Jujian's [1300] son-in-law and Lu(9) Xiji [1305] was Qian Xuan's [7142] son-in-law. Xiji was the elder brother of Xichun, Shouzhi's grandfather-in-law! There are no other indications that Shouzhi was related to any of the many branches of the Wuxing Qian. I am, however, assigning him as the only member of a jia 'p' and as a lineal descendant of Feng [16171].</note>
